5|$|The term hatt-ı hümayun is {{occasionally}} used in {{the literal}} sense of the handwriting of the Sultan. For example, the imperial poet Nef'i has written a masnavi of 22 couplets describing the calligraphy of Sultan Murad IV, called Der-Vasf-ı Hatt-ı Humayun-ı Sultan Murad Han. The whole poem is a compliment to <b>the</b> <b>writings</b> <b>of</b> <b>the</b> Sultan.|$|E
